Sunday Times Says No Law Broken in Brown Flat Purchase Story

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-12T17:35:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/sunday-times-says-no-law-broken-in-brown-flat-purchase-story.html
News International’s Sunday Times
newspaper said its story about former Prime Minister  Gordon Brown ’s purchase of an apartment was “pursued in the public
interest,” and “no law was broken in the process of this
investigation” and “no criminal was used.” A spokesperson for
the newspaper made the comments in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 